AGI - Recognize the daily therapeutic, rehabilitative and social commitment of the therapeutic and socio-rehabilitative psychiatry communities of Lazio with the adaptation of the regional 'tariffs', sustained in 2009, at the cost of life. This is the request of the employees of the structures accredited by the Lazio Region.
&nbsp;
In an open letter sent to President Francesco Rocca and the Minister of Health, Orazio Schillaci, the associations representing the workers of the sector, and that Tuesday 11 February will manifest with a sit-in right in front of the headquarters of the Lazio Region in via Rosa Raimondi Garibaldi in Rome, they ask for measures that guarantee the survival of these realities to protect the same psychiatric patients who risk to end "in places of care similar to the old asylums - they write the associations - that only closed Anascop, Confepi, Confcooperative Health Lazio, Federlazio, Mito e Realtà, Structures Federate Reverie and Fenascop.
&nbsp;
"The needy recognition of the almost fifty-year therapeutic, rehabilitation and social commitment of the therapeutic and socio-rehabilitative psychiatric communities which, with the closure of the asylums, have given the start to the realization of psychiatric reform strongly desired by Basaglia - reads in the letter sent by the associations - is now marking the step because of the loss of attention of the Regional Health Administration and the public opinion
&nbsp;
"The mental discomfort / mental illness is a monster with multiple heads that in order to be treated requires basic skills in understanding psychological therapy - writes the coordination of associations - continuous training of operators, strong motivations in the proper care, dedication and economic means. Instead we go back to talk and practice electroshock and add violent suffering and removal instead of listening, dialogue, understanding and care."
&nbsp;
The operators of the sector point their finger on the "failure of economic recognition for the management of this type of structures that are private, even if accredited, do not enjoy the structural and economic assets of which enjoy the public structures that live and operate with budgets, and costs, much more substantial". The operators therefore ask for a "period updating of the rates according to indices related to the increase in the cost of life and of the productive factors, as it happens periodically in all the productive sectors and also, in particular, in health".
&nbsp;
"For the therapeutic and socio-rehabilitative communities in psychiatry, however, this adjustment has been forgotten and is likely to be an obsolete and disregarded right - we still read - the adjustment of the tariff, laws of the fees, is blocked in 2009, that is, 16 years ago, we now enter in the 17th year". "Therapeutic and socio-rehabilitative communities in psychiatry have the right to be treated like all other care realities - conclude - that they have already achieved all tariff adjustments, allowing them to retain all quality requirements having had the adjustment of the fees".&nbsp;

