&nbsp;
<div </div
&nbsp;
The man, promptly stopped by the Vatican Gendarmerie, is native to Romania. Delivered to the staff of the Vatican Inspectorate, he was identified and denounced. It is not the first time they happen in the Basilica undesirable gestures. A similar episode occurred on September 4, 2019: always under the Baldacchino, a fifty-year-old of Santa Marinella, was stopped after he climbed the altar and threw a candlestick on the ground. &nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;
"This is an episode this morning (Friday, October 7, ndr), a person with severe psychic disabilities, was taken into custody by the Vatican Gendarmerie and delivered to the Italian authorities." The Director of the Press Office of the Holy See Matteo Bruni said so.
